Saudi Arabia sends 50 million dollars aid to quake-hit Turkey
2011-10-27 22:17:14 GMT
RIYADH, Oct. 27 (Xinhua) -- Saudi King Abdullah bin Abdulaziz Al Saud ordered on Thursday to offer 50 million U.S. dollars in aid for turkey to overcome the effects of Sunday's powerful earthquake.King Abdullah issued the order to offer the funds "to help the Turkish Republic as efforts are ongoing to overcome the earthquake that hit Van province in eastern turkey," the state-run SPA news agency reported.The order came as "feature for the Saudi steady and lasting stances for helping affected people, standing beside them and mitigating their sufferings", according the SPA.The death toll from Sunday's earthquake has risen to 534 and the number of the injured to 2,300, according the latest figures released by Turkey's Disaster and Emergency Administration (AFAD) Thursday.
